title: Denmark Terms of Trade
description: Terms of Trade in Denmark decreased to 111.70 points in September from 113.90 points in August of 2022. Terms of Trade in Denmark averaged 99.45 points from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 115.20 points in June of 2021 and a record low of 93.80 points in March of 1998. In Denmark, Terms of Trade (ToT) correspond to the ratio of Price of exportable goods to the Price of importable goods. This page provides - Denmark Terms of Trade - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Statistics Denmark
